(S'SITUATION During August, no locusts were seen during surveys   in the interior and on the Red Sea coast near Rabigh  (2247N/3901E) and Qunfidah (1909N/4107E). On  the 30th, there were unconfirmed reports of locusts  in many places on the Red Sea coast south of Jizan  (1656N/4233E).'
p10
S'FORECAST Scattered adults are likely to appear on the   southern coast of the Red Sea between Qunfidah and  Jizan, and breed on a small scale in areas of recent  rainfall. There is a risk that a few swarms could arrive  in these areas from Yemen.'
