p37
(S'SITUATION No locusts were seen during surveys that   commenced on 13 August northeast of Tombouctou  (1649N/0259W), in the Timetrine near Ti-n-kar  (1926N/0022W), and in the Adrar des Iforas near  Tessalit (2011N/0102E), Aguelhoc (1927N/0052E)  and between Kidal (1827N/0125E) and Tin Essako  (1826N/0229E). All surveys were halted on the 26th  after one team was attacked north of Gao.'
p38
S'FORECAST Scattered adults are likely to be present and   breeding north of Tombouctou and in parts of the  northeast (Timetrine, Tilemsi Valley, Adrar des Iforas  and Tamesna). Small-scale breed will continue in  these areas and cause locust numbers to increase  slightly.'
