sS'Pakistan'
p65
(S'SITUATION During the second half of July, scattered mature   adults persisted in the Khairpur and Cholistan desert  between the Indus River Valley and the Indian border  as well as in the Lasbela (2614N/6619E) area west of  Karachi.  During the first half of August, limited hatching   occurred at two places near the Indian border  southeast of Rahimyar Khan (2822N/7020E).  Scattered mature adults persisted in Khairpur and  Cholistan.'
p66
S'FORECAST Small-scale breeding will continue in Cholistan and  Khairpur with further hatching, causing locust numbers  to increase slightly. Fledglings and immature adults  will appear from early September onwards. Similar  breeding is probably underway and will continue in  Tharparkar. There is a very low possibility that a few  small swarms could arrive from Yemen via Oman  during the first half of September. Thereafter, this  threat should pass.'
